  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6772.45 sitting between the massive negative gamma walls at 6770 (-16.6B) and 6765 (-16.9B), dealers are currently in buy mode as they're short gamma below the 6780 positive gamma peak. The 1193% 1-minute GEX surge and wall break event suggests violent dealer rebalancing is underway, with dealers aggressively buying this dip to hedge their short gamma exposure. Key inflection point is the 6780 max positive gamma level—if SPX rallies back above there, dealers flip to selling mode, but any further weakness toward 6765-6760 triggers accelerated dealer buying.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect strong buying support here with potential for a sharp bounce back toward 6780.",
